    <span xlink:href="10640_2018_231_Article_IEq34.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> and suppose 
  <div id="IEq35" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M85" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ \hat{V}_{L}^{A} &gt; 0, $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M86" class="math">
     <div class="mrow">
      <div class="msubsup">
       <div accent="true" class="mover">
        <span class="mi">V</span>
        <span stretchy="false" class="mo">^</span>
       </div>
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mi">L</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mi">A</span>
      </div>
      <span class="mo">&gt;</span>
      <span class="mn">0</span>
      <span class="mo">,</span>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="10640_2018_231_Article_IEq35.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> so that the total marginal return on adaptation capital is decreasing in 
  <span class="italic">L</span> and increasing in 
  <span class="italic">K</span>, i.e. 
  <div id="IEq36" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M87" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ V_{LL}^{A} &lt; 0 $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M88" class="math">
     <div class="mrow">
      <div class="msubsup">
